# Versioning and Releases

## Semantic Versioning
- Follow semantic versioning (MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH) for all modules
- **MAJOR**: Breaking changes to API, state structure, or consensus
- **MINOR**: New features, backward-compatible API additions
- **PATCH**: Bug fixes, backward-compatible changes
- Go modules: `v1.2.3` format in `go.mod`
- Protobuf: Version in package name (e.g., `volnix.ident.v1`)
- Cosmos SDK: Align with SDK version (v0.53.x)

## Release Process
- Pre-release: All tests passing, security audit, documentation updated, changelog generated
- Release tags: `v<version>` for full releases, `v<module>-<version>` for module-specific
- Maintain `CHANGELOG.md` following [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/) format
- Categories: Added, Changed, Deprecated, Removed, Fixed, Security

## Migrations
- Implement `AppModule.AppModuleMigrationHandler` interface
- Test migrations on testnet before mainnet
- Document breaking changes and provide upgrade instructions
- Maintain compatibility layer when possible

## Version Management
- Each module has independent versioning
- Pin Cosmos SDK: `v0.53.x`, CometBFT: `v0.38.x`
- Coordinate major version bumps across modules
- Document version compatibility matrix
